messages.msgSnippet: In a message dated 9/14/02 8:25:04 AM, starsuncloud@cs.com writes:
messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 9/14/02 8:25:04 AM, starsuncloud@... writes:

<< I see our garbage can has been knocked over and all the garbage is out,
but I
don't want to walk out there to get it. I'm being a wimp! >>

But it will be gone soon and you'll have someone else's garbage, right?


We pick our neighbors' pieces of trash out of our side yard because of the
direction of wind and such here. So I do get to see some school papers and
notes from teachers, and I wish they would learn to use trash bags instead of
just putting their lives loose in the dumpster.

I hope the storm spared all your trees and windows.

Sandra

messages.subject: TS Hannah

messages.messageBody:
Well here we are in the middle of Tropical Storm Hannah. The wind is a
blowin' and we're supposed to get 8 inches of rain. Our little pond in back
is full to bursting!
Are you getting any of this Sharon?
It's been a while since we've had a storm, so it's kinda exciting. As long as
none of our huge pine trees fall on the house :)
I see our garbage can has been knocked over and all the garbage is out, but I
don't want to walk out there to get it. I'm being a wimp!
Life in Florida.....ain't it grand?

Ren
